# tree-sitter@0.21 (root devDep) vs tree-sitter@^0.25 (peerOptional of
# tree-sitter-python@0.23.6) create an npm ERESOLVE conflict in strict mode.
# Both packages work fine at runtime — tree-sitter-python's peerOptional
# constraint is overly aggressive. legacy-peer-deps=true falls back to npm 6
# resolution (warn, don't fail) which matches what we want here.
#
# Reproduce without this: `npm ci` fails on:
#   ERESOLVE could not resolve
#   While resolving: tree-sitter-python@0.23.6
#   Found: tree-sitter@0.21.1
legacy-peer-deps=true
